ion.\\n```suggestion\\n\\tinfoBytes, err := json.Marshal(session.Info)\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to marshal session info for chunking: %w\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\t// Base JSON structure size: {\\\"info\\\":<info>,\\\"messages\\\":[ ... ]}\\n\\tcurrentSize := len(`{\\\"info\\\":`) + len(infoBytes) + len(`,\\\"messages\\\":[`) + len(\\\"]}\\\")\\n```\\n---\\n**Copilot** on `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/opencode.go`:85\\nSilently skipping messages that fail to marshal could lead to data loss. If a message cannot be marshaled, this is likely a significant error that should be reported. Consider returning an error or at least logging a warning when messages are skipped.\\n```suggestion\\n\\t\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to marshal message for chunking: %w\\\", err)\\n```\\n---\\n**Copilot** on `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/opencode.go`:125\\nThe ReassembleTranscript function returns (nil, nil) for empty chunks slice, which violates the nilnil linter rule. This is inconsistent with the handling in ChunkTranscript which returns an error for zero chunks. Consider returning an error here instead: `return nil, errors.New(\\\"no chunks to reassemble\\\")`\\n```suggestion\\n\\t\\treturn nil, errors.New(\\\"no chunks to reassemble\\\")\\n```\\n---\\n**Copilot** on `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/hooks.go`:852\\nError handling is being silently ignored in three places within the test helper. While this might be acceptable for test code in some cases, it makes debugging test failures difficult. Consider at least logging errors to t.Logf() when os.ReadFile, os.MkdirAll, or os.WriteFile fail, so test failures are easier to diagnose.\\n```suggestion\\n\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\t\\tr.T.Logf(\\\"SimulateOpenCodeTurnEnd: failed to read transcript from %q: %v\\\", transcriptPath, err)\\n\\t\\t} else {\\n\\t\\t\\tdestDir := filepath.Join(r.RepoDir, \\\".entire\\\", \\\"tmp\\\")\\n\\t\\t\\tif mkErr := os.MkdirAll(destDir, 0o755); mkErr != nil {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tr.T.Logf(\\\"SimulateOpenCodeTurnEnd: failed to create directory %q: %v\\\", destDir, mkErr)\\n\\t\\t\\t} else {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdestPath := filepath.Join(destDir, sessionID+\\\".json\\\")\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tif writeErr := os.WriteFile(destPath, srcData, 0o644); writeErr != nil {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tr.T.Logf(\\\"SimulateOpenCodeTurnEnd: failed to write transcript to %q: %v\\\", destPath, writeErr)\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n```\\n---\\n**cursor[bot]** on `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`:209\\n### Missing export.json write breaks resume/rewind for OpenCode\\n**High Severity**\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->\\nThe old code in `lifecycle.go` copied the OpenCode export JSON to `export.json` in the session metadata directory during TurnEnd (the removed `exportSrc` block). The new code removed this logic entirely, but `extractSessionData` in `manual_commit_condensation.go` still reads `ExportData` from `metadataDir/export.json` (lines 429–437). Since that file is never written, `ExportData` will always be empty during condensation, breaking resume/rewind for OpenCode sessions because the committed checkpoint won't contain the data needed by `opencode import`.\\n<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->\\n<!-- BUGBOT_BUG_ID: 9f48dd01-f335-4a58-801f-d89747690439 -->\\n<!-- LOCATIONS START\\ncmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go#L198-L207\\ncmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go#L428-L437\\nLOCATIONS END -->\\n<details>\\n<summary>Additional Locations (1)</summary>\\n- [`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go#L428-L437`](https://github.REDACTED.go#L428-L437)\\n</details>\\n<p><a href=\\\"https://cursor.com/open?REDACTED\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\"><picture><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-dark.png\\\"><source media=\\\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\\\" srcset=\\\"https://cursor.com/assets/images/fix-in-cursor-light.png\\\"><img alt=\\\"Fix in Cursor\\\" width=\\\"115\\\" he